rd.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showMessage?topicID=12.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;|  </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top background=http://www.graffe.com/home/bar_back.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.graffe.com/home/bar_back.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/12/01 8:13:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Staff of the Wheel vs. Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> Someone asked why, so I'll start a debate.<br>
<br>
Staff of the Wheel or Weeping Wand? Each has an advantage...<br>
<br>
SotW: +10 Int +10 HP +10 Mana 10/100 1HB<br>
<br>
   Nice on the Mana and trade skills.<br>
<br>
WW:   +3 Int +3 AC 5/25 1HB<br>
<br>
   FOCUS ITEM for Dodge and channeling.<br>
<br>
I vote WW for any situation I think I may get hit. One more successful DD while being smacked, or getting Gate to work when I most need it is much more valuable thanthe extra 50 or so mana. <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Journeyman Slayer<BR>
Asigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqorbeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>QorbeQ</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 5:30:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the Wheel vs. Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> Seeing as I'm one of the only people reading... what's a Focus Item? I've occasionally heard of them but know nothing about them at all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 8:43:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the Wheel vs. Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> A focus item improves the thing they focus on. The best example are the focus items for Mages. The Shovel of Pondz(?) is an item that improves the power if an earth elemental when summoned. The weeping wand is a Focus for channeling and dodge it seems, although I have heard rumor it improves evocation as well. I personally do not believe that, however. <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Journeyman Slayer<BR>
Asigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=yiliamar>Yiliamar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 8:47:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the Wheel vs. Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> Hmm... I always thought they called it a focus because of the int on it, and useful for dodge because of the 3 ac.  Not much in either, but some times it's enough.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 12:17:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Weeping Wand as a focus</span><hr size=1> When I carry the WW I notice a substantial change in channeling and dodge. Whee I might get one spell off with channeling every few hours previously, with the wand I have actually come to rely on one per fight. And I now actually notice my dodging  it happens so often. That is to say, I would get it maybe once a day without and now I have seen it happen more than once in a fight. Now maybe I'm insane, but if it is true, I'll take those over int in a fight any day. <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Journeyman Slayer<BR>
Asigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxendapus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendapus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/01 3:08:20 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weeping Wand as a focus</span><hr size=1> I never thought much of the WW from the stats and prefered my sacrificial dagger for the INT, might be worth looking into the quest if what you say is true though, although I was looking to do the staff of the wheel before I read this haven't started that yet, rather have my tempflux staff above anything right now too.<br>
<br>
However just a question of the WW, the description on graffes here says it has 2 charges of strip enchantment and mentions nothing of a focus item, also i thought verant stated they would not put items in game that directly improved a players skill rating (which is why people say tinkered lock picks don't improve skill or roll) which you suggest this does. The mage focus improves the pet *shrug*.<br>
<br>
Still i guess it might be worth doing the quest if i come across the drops to test your theory. I did however find that maxing dodge early helped with negating interupts and usings lots of the skin line of spells. Gate seems to channel more than it used to also, but people have suggested the lower level of the spell the easier it is to channel. <p>Xendapus Fabink.<BR> Adventurer, Explorer, Battle Wizard & Bartender (Part-time). <BR> Witch Hunter & Field Operative for the Eldritch Collective. <BR>Devotee of the Burning Prince.
 Master Tinkerer.<BR>
Founding Director of Fabink's Incredible Gadgets and Gizmos inc. <BR>Connoisseur of the Usti 'Kahe PIE Selection. <BR> Proud Member of the Coeur de Lion.</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uxendapus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xendapus</A> at: 6/14/01 4:45:07 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uennyaorcsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ennya Orcsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/15/01 1:06:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Staff of the Wheel vs. Weeping Wand</span><hr size=1> As with all things I 'notice' It is possible that I'm more sensitive to watching now than I was before. The SoTF is a quest I need only one more part for, sadly Solusek's Eye is a Nasty place. (This is why we're raiding it on the 23rd on Morell Thule. If you're interested, please send me an email ennyaorcsbane@yahoo.com :)<br>
<br>
I believe the Focus part comes from the fact that the NPC that assigns the quest actually says it's a wizard focus. (Unlike the rest of the Items I have found.) On Allakazahms(sp) messages there are mentions about it being a focus, but also claims that it's an evocation focus.<br>
<br>
*shrug* In the big picture, I'm not sure it even matters. I&quot;m not casting any spells that require the small amounts of mana that extra int gives. As part of a full set, it's always good to get a few extra here and there, but the mana change from an Int of 163 and 169 just isn't that much.<br>
<br>
If you do get it, let us know if you notice any differences.<br>
 <p>Ennya Orcsbane<BR>
1st Elder of The Tears Of Veeshan<BR>
Journeyman Slayer<BR>
Asigner of the Hunt<BR>
Wizardess<BR></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.showMessage?topicID=12.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.emailToFriend?topicID=4.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.threadControl?topicID=4.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm24.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=4.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm22">Out of Mana<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm27">PVP Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm28">The Library<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm25">Share Your Mana<option value="graffeswizard